what the fuck I'm doing here.

06:37.623 --> 06:39.461
Gotta be aggressive.

06:39.530 --> 06:41.463
I... I did my research
on the Major.

06:41.531 --> 06:43.265
He says
you wanna win this thing,

06:43.333 --> 06:45.063
you gotta be raring to rip.

06:46.029 --> 06:48.505
Fuck, boys, I am raring to rip.

06:48.574 --> 06:50.841
(MIMICS HANK) "Fuck, boys,
I am raring to rip."

06:50.910 --> 06:53.068
(ALL CHUCKLING)

06:53.137 --> 06:54.311
-Hey, fuck you.
-PETER: Just sound like

06:54.380 --> 06:56.011
-what you said, asshole.
-Raring to rip.

06:56.080 --> 06:57.244
(CHUCKLES) Yeah.

06:57.313 --> 06:58.615
You sound like my...

06:58.683 --> 07:00.950
(CHUCKLING) my meemaw
on the bowl in morning, man.

07:01.019 --> 07:02.047
Right, guys?

07:06.058 --> 07:07.623
The fuck is a "meemaw"?

07:07.692 --> 07:10.022
Fuck you. (CHUCKLING)
I was just fucking around.

07:11.723 --> 07:12.788
Hey, here he comes.

07:12.857 --> 07:14.763
(DISTANT ENGINE WHIRRING)

07:17.861 --> 07:20.537
(TENSE MUSIC PLAYING)

07:20.606 --> 07:23.904
(STUTTERING) Shit on a stick.
It's the Major.

07:31.577 --> 07:32.814
(ENGINE STOPS)

07:34.514 --> 07:36.816
Sit down, boys.

07:36.885 --> 07:39.885
-Keep hint 13 in mind.
-HANK: Hint number 13.

07:39.953 --> 07:41.191
That's conserve energy
whenever possible.

07:41.259 --> 07:42.326
PETER: Yeah, shut up, Olson.

07:42.395 --> 07:44.858
-We all read the rulebook.
-MAJOR: Now,

07:44.927 --> 07:48.725
as I call your name,
step forward and take your tags.

07:48.794 --> 07:50.668
Put 'em around your neck,

07:50.737 --> 07:54.572
and then go back to your place
until I instruct otherwise.

07:55.768 --> 07:58.609
Ewing, James. Number one.

07:59.376 --> 08:01.744
Smith, Patrick. Number four.

08:03.480 --> 08:06.309
Barkovitch, Gary. Number five.

08:08.880 --> 08:11.589
Baker, Arthur. Number six.

08:13.821 --> 08:17.419
White, "Curly" Adam.
Number seven.

08:20.562 --> 08:24.030
Sanders, Rank. Number 19.

08:27.173 --> 08:30.971
McVries, Peter. Number 23.

08:33.476 --> 08:36.306
Stebbins, Billy. Number 38.

08:40.085 --> 08:41.443
Good luck, son.

08:42.913 --> 08:47.388
Olson, Hank. Number 46.

08:47.456 --> 08:51.123
Garraty, Raymond. 47.

08:54.662 --> 08:57.536
Parker, Collie. Number 48.

09:00.207 --> 09:04.004
Harkness, Richard. Number 49.

09:05.937 --> 09:08.310
Fellas, line up by fives,

09:08.378 --> 09:10.241
in no particular order.

09:12.709 --> 09:14.410
Boys,

09:14.479 --> 09:19.288
it takes heavy, heavy sac
to sign up for this contest,

09:19.356 --> 09:20.991
and you've all got it.

09:21.060 --> 09:22.319
You're men now.

09:24.129 --> 09:25.656
As you all know,

09:25.725 --> 09:27.222
our country has been

09:27.290 --> 09:28.757
in a period
of financial struggle

09:28.826 --> 09:29.992
since the war,

09:30.061 --> 09:31.635
and we did the first Long Walk

09:31.704 --> 09:35.469
all those years ago
to inspire and reintegrate

09:35.537 --> 09:37.775
the value of work ethic.

09:37.843 --> 09:41.403
Each year after the event,
there's a spike in production.

09:41.472 --> 09:45.276
We have the means
to return to our former glory.

09:46.052 --> 09:47.944
Our problem now,

09:48.012 --> 09:51.788
is an epidemic of laziness.

09:52.521 --> 09:54.819
You boys are the answer.

09:54.887 --> 09:57.528
The Long Walk is the answer.

09:57.597 --> 10:00.294
When this is broadcast
for all the states,

10:00.363 --> 10:01.930
your inspiration

10:01.999 --> 10:06.196
will continue to elevate
our gross national product.

10:06.265 --> 10:10.204
We will be number one
in the world again!

10:10.273 --> 10:11.643
ALL: Yeah!

10:12.838 --> 10:14.436
MAJOR: Now, uh...

10:14.505 --> 10:16.972
I'm not going to go through
the whole rulebook,

10:17.041 --> 10:19.517
but it boils down to this.

10:19.585 --> 10:22.618
Walk until there's
only one of you left.

10:22.687 --> 10:25.689
Maintain a speed
of three miles per hour.

10:25.758 --> 10:29.284
If you fall below the speed,
you get a warning.

10:29.353 --> 10:30.987
If you can't make speed
in ten seconds,

10:31.056 --> 10:33.123
you get an additional warning.

10:33.192 --> 10:35.628
Three warnings,
you get your ticket.

10:35.696 --> 10:37.730
Walk one hour at speed,

10:37.799 --> 10:40.161
one warning is erased and so on.

10:40.230 --> 10:43.001
If you step off the pavement,

10:43.070 --> 10:46.409
you will get your ticket
without warning.

10:46.478 --> 10:49.579
The goal is to last the longest.

10:49.648 --> 10:53.480
There's one winner
and no finish line.

10:53.549 --> 10:55.247
Any of you can win.

10:55.815 --> 10:56.850
Any of you can do it

10:56.918 --> 10:58.921
if you walk long
and steady enough.

10:59.886 --> 11:02.724
If you refuse to give up.

11:02.793 --> 11:04.619
I look at each
and every one of you,

11:06.132 --> 11:08.095
and I see hope.

11:08.925 --> 11:10.157
Now, boys,

11:10.226 --> 11:11.895
who's set to fucking win?

11:11.964 --> 11:13.901
-(ALL CHEERING)
-I said...

11:13.970 --> 11:17.808
-who's ready to fucking win?
-(ALL CHEERING)

11:18.773 --> 11:21.174
(UPLIFTING MUSIC PLAYING)

11:29.280 --> 11:31.613
MAJOR: Luck to all,
and remember,

11:32.653 --> 11:35.056
